HB 786 Original 2026 Regular Session Egan
Abstract: Provides for the prohibited use of certain processes for healthcare provider
payment claims.
Present law provides that the provisions of the present law shall not be waived by contract
and any contractual clause in conflict with the provisions of the present law or purports to
waive any requirements of the present law is void.
Proposed law amends present law, defines extrapolation, and strictly prohibits extrapolation
use by healthcare providers to complete audits and audit estimates.
Proposed law makes technical changes.
(Amends R.S. 46:460.75(C)-(E); Adds R.S. 46:460.75(F))
